<DOC><DOCNO> SJMN91-06105049 </DOCNO><ACCESS> 06105049 </ACCESS><CAPTION>  Photos (2); PHOTO: Associated Press; The Haven burns after explosions hit thetanker Saturday near Genoa; three sailors have died; PHOTO: Associated Press;A tugboat fights fires on the Haven  </CAPTION><DESCRIPT>  ITALY; OIL; BOAT; ACCIDENT  </DESCRIPT><LEADPARA>  A huge explosion and two smaller blasts rocked a burning tanker Saturday,heightening fears that the sinking vessel could break apart and spill millionsof gallons of oil onto the Italian Riviera.;    In Rome, the governmentdeclared a state of emergency, making the region eligible for special aid.There was no estimate on the amount of oil spilled from the Haven, which wasloaded with nearly 41 million gallons of crude oil when it began burningThursday.  </LEADPARA><SECTION>  Front  </SECTION><HEADLINE>  BLASTS ADD TO FEARS OF HUGE OIL SPILL  </HEADLINE><TEXT>     The tanker was set ablaze by an explosion in a holding tank that had justbeen unloaded, authorities said.;    The fire on the Haven killed threesailors and three were missing late Saturday. Twenty-nine crew members whojumped overboard were hospitalized with burns and smoke inhalation, 11 of themin critical condition.;    Port officials in Leghorn, Italy, said a secondtanker continued to burn about 85 miles to the southeast of Genoa.;    TheAgip Abruzzo was carrying 24 million gallons of oil when it was rammed by theferry Moby Prince late Wednesday and both ships caught fire. As many as 151people aboard the ferry died.  </TEXT><BYLINE>  Associated Press  </BYLINE><COUNTRY>  USA  </COUNTRY><CITY>  Genoa, Italy  </CITY><EDITION>  Morning Final  </EDITION><CODE>  SJ  </CODE><NAME>  San Jose Mercury News  </NAME><PUBDATE>   910414  </PUBDATE> <DAY>  Sunday  </DAY><MONTH>  April  </MONTH><PG.COL>  17A  </PG.COL><PUBYEAR>  1991  </PUBYEAR><REGION>  WEST  </REGION><FEATURE>  PHOTO  </FEATURE><STATE>  CA  </STATE><WORD.CT>  215  </WORD.CT><DATELINE>  Sunday April 14, 199100105049,SJ1  <